div1.p:
John Best
thus deposed: I am Servant to the Duchess of Leedes. Between Nine and Ten at Night, as her Grace was at Supper in the Back-Parlour, (at her House in Pall-mall
) I heard a little Noise in the Fore-Parlour, where I had left the Candle burning: I stept in and saw Cliff standing there. He presently got out of the Sash-Window, and I after him; for the Sash was then thrown up; but it was shut close but a little before. I cry'd, Stop Thief; and in pursuing him, this Cloak was taken up.
